/* Influence in culture */ The Nazi party is much more known as the "Nazi Party". Also, it had very little to do with socialism (it was close to the opposite), so using the original name can be unnecessarily confusing for less knowledgable readers and should be left to be mentioned in the article about the party. It's like saying "German Democratic Republic" instead of "East Germany", which was very far from being democratic. Added "German" to keep that adjective to help the reader.
